  "response_text": "The commercial opens on a dark, arcade-style sign. Against a black background, a bright yellow starburst frames large red-orange words reading “PIZZA” above and “GAME” below, with “Delivery” written across the middle in white script. Smaller yellow burst shapes sit around the edges, reinforcing the look of a game cabinet or carnival sign. A lower strip briefly comes into view with partially visible wording about delivered pizza.\n\nThe scene changes to a game-screen-like display. At the top, a yellow burst contains the red word “BEST,” followed by white block letters reading “DELIVERED PIZZA.” Below it, the screen is filled with a neat grid of many small Domino’s Pizza box logos, each tilted diagonally on a black background. A bright green triangular beam sweeps in from the left, like a laser or spotlight aimed across the grid. The Domino’s logos remain arranged in rows, red and blue rectangles with the white domino-dot emblem and “Domino’s Pizza” text. As the green light moves across them, the image briefly takes on a speckled green, electrical-looking interference, then returns to the clean grid of Domino’s boxes. Another green beam appears from the upper right and points down toward the logos, but the rows of Domino’s boxes still remain intact.\n\nA red animated character, identifiable from the commercial context as the Noid, appears against a dark, colorful, out-of-focus background. He is a small, puppet-like figure in a tight red suit with long floppy rabbit-like ears or horns, a tan face, a bulbous nose, wide white eyes, and a round emblem on his chest. Seen first in profile, he looks tense and watchful. Then green light washes over him. He faces forward with both gloved hands raised, fingers spread, as if startled or trying to protect himself. His face is tinted green, his eyes widen, and his mouth opens. For a moment, glowing green electric scribbles or energy lines wrap around his body and limbs, making him look shocked or zapped.\n\nThe green effect disappears, and the Noid is shown normally again. His mouth hangs open, one ear stretches sideways, and his expression shifts from alarmed to defeated. He looks around with drooping, worried eyes as his long ears sag and wobble. By the end of this sequence, he faces forward with a tired, resigned look.\n\nThe final image is a close-up of a pizza covered with melted cheese and toppings, including pepperoni, mushrooms, black olives, green peppers, and browned crumbled meat. Over the lower left is the Domino’s Pizza logo, and across the bottom in large white cursive script is the slogan “Nobody Delivers Better,” underlined with a sweeping stroke and marked with a small service mark. The pizza remains as the warm, appetizing background while the Domino’s branding and slogan stay prominently on screen.",
